President Barack Obama has proclaimed October 2012 as National Arts and Humanities Month. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of the arts and humanities in American society, highlighting their ability to bring people together, challenge perceptions, and teach important lessons. The President also expresses his commitment to strengthening arts and humanities programs in schools and communities across the country. He calls upon the people of the United States to observe the month with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs to celebrate the arts and humanities in America.